headline: Venessa Harrison elected to Southern Company Gas Board of Directors
summary: Southern Company Gas today announced that Venessa Harrison, former president of AT&T's Southeast Coastal States, has been elected to the company's board of directors, effective April 24.

headline: PG&E (PCG) Q1 Earnings and Revenues Miss Estimates
summary: PG&E (PCG) delivered earnings and revenue surprises of -5.71% and 2.06%, respectively, for the quarter ended March 2025. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?
